---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "ILVE Stove Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "ILVE stove repair across SoCal, Majestic III, Nostalgie II, Panoramagic, Milano, Roma, Torino, Professional Plus. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/ilve-stove-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is ILVE still a family-owned Italian brand?",
    a: "Yes, ILVE is an independent Italian family-owned manufacturer based in <b>Treviso region, northeast Italy</b>, founded in 1975 and still privately held. ILVE is distinct from Smeg and Bertazzoni (both Guastalla-based Emilia-Romagna families), different region, different product positioning, different family ownership. ILVE's independence matters for service: product decisions and engineering priorities are made by the family, not by a corporate conglomerate. For parts distribution in North America, ILVE works through specialized importers that maintain parts inventories for current and prior-generation ILVE lines. Lead times for specialty parts run 2-4 weeks when Italian factory sourcing is needed; common service components (igniters, thermocouples, burner caps, oven elements) are typically stocked at US distribution and ship 5-10 days. Color-matched parts can run longer depending on specific color availability."
  },
  {
    q: "Which ILVE stove lines are most common in LA?",
    a: "<b>Majestic III</b> is the current-generation flagship and by volume the most-installed ILVE stove in LA, 30\"/36\"/40\"/48\"/60\" freestanding dual-fuel + all-gas configurations, available in 60+ color + finish combinations (knobs in stainless / chrome / brass / copper / bronze trim). <b>Nostalgie II</b> is the vintage-inspired line with rounded-corner styling and brass / chrome knob detail, common in traditional-design kitchens. <b>Panoramagic</b> adds the panoramic-view tilt oven-door design. <b>Milano, Roma, Torino</b> are entry-luxury lines at smaller formats. <b>Professional Plus</b> is the pro-style flagship with heavier build + higher BTU burners. ILVE installs concentrate in Bel Air + Beverly Hills design-forward custom kitchens, Santa Monica + Venice architectural remodels, Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-district homes, Pasadena + San Marino heritage kitchens. Color-matched ILVE is a visual-focal-point choice, red, blue, burgundy, and custom pastels are LA-common."
  },
  {
    q: "ILVE gas burner not lighting properly, what's the usual fix?",
    a: "Order of diagnostic: (1) orifice sizing, European-spec orifices don't always match US natural gas / LP pressure; mismatch is common on imported ILVE or rental/sold-home units where fuel type changed. Orifice swap $180–$280 per burner. (2) Spark-module / ignitor, ILVE spark modules age at 8-12 year mark, swap $280–$400; ignitor tip clean or replace $200–$300 when carbon / electrode wear. (3) Burner cap seating, ILVE burner caps have precise alignment; reseating often free at diagnostic. (4) Thermocouple flame-failure device, EU-spec safety device cuts gas if flame not detected; thermocouple $220–$320. (5) Gas valve restriction $300–$440. (6) Regulator pressure $220–$320. Our techs carry ILVE-specific igniters + thermocouples in LA dispatch. 80% of ILVE no-light complaints resolve at orifice + spark + thermocouple verification."
  },
  {
    q: "ILVE oven temperature inaccurate, what's failing?",
    a: "Order: (1) oven temperature sensor, sensor drift is the #1 cause at 5-10 year mark; sensor swap $220–$320; (2) thermostat on units with analog dial thermostats (older Nostalgie, entry lines), thermostat swap $280–$400; (3) control board on digital-control Majestic III / Panoramagic, board swap $480–$660; (4) bake element (electric oven-side on dual-fuel ILVE), element swap $320–$460; (5) convection fan motor, affects cycle target on convection bake; motor swap $340–$500; (6) thermal fuse or high-limit safety cutout $240–$340; (7) oven door seal, rope seal degradation allows heat leak; seal swap $180–$280. ILVE oven cavity on Majestic III is larger than most 30\" competitors (European-format wider cavity), which affects temperature-distribution diagnostic, we verify temp at 4 corners + center during sensor calibration."
  },
  {
    q: "How does ILVE service compare to Viking or Wolf economics?",
    a: "Individual part pricing runs comparable to Viking + Wolf, ignitor, thermocouple, sensor, element, control board all within 10-20% of Viking / Wolf equivalents. Where ILVE service economics diverge: (1) specialty parts lead time 2-4 weeks from Italian factory when not in US distribution stock (common service components ship 5-10 days); (2) color-matched exterior panel service can run longer depending on specific color availability; (3) European-spec gas configuration complications occasionally require specific orifice sizing. Offsetting those factors: ILVE build quality on Majestic III + Professional Plus is at luxury-tier standards, so actual service frequency tends to be moderate, common service items (igniter, sensor, thermocouple) at 7-10 year marks rather than earlier. 20-25 year service life on Majestic III platform with periodic parts servicing is realistic. Diagnostic pricing standard residential $89 waived with repair."
  },
  {
    q: "Our ILVE is 20+ years old, is it still serviceable?",
    a: "In most cases yes. ILVE's earlier platforms (pre-Majestic III) used simpler analog thermostats + mechanical spark ignition that's more straightforward to service than current digital-control units. Parts availability on 15-20+ year ILVE is a mixed picture: common mechanical components (burner caps, thermocouples, thermostats, gas valves) are generally still sourceable through Italian factory aftermarket; specific generation-era control boards on mid-2000s digital ILVE can be tougher to source (occasional substitution through cross-reference). Rebuild economics on a 20-year ILVE: burner refurbishment (orifices + caps + thermocouples) $500–$900; oven-side package (thermostat + sensor + element + door seal) $700–$1,200; full $89 diagnostic + parts quoted. Rebuild totals typical $1,400–$2,400 on sound older units. Replacement new Majestic III 36\" dual-fuel runs $7,000–$11,000 retail, rebuild math usually favors rebuild when the body is in sound condition and color / finish matters to the household."
  },
  {
    q: "Color-matched ILVE panel damaged, what's the replacement process?",
    a: "ILVE's 60+ color program runs through Italian factory color-matching. Current-generation Majestic III colors in stock through US distribution usually ship 2-4 weeks; less-common colors or legacy colors that require Italian-factory sourcing can run 6-10 weeks. At diagnostic we: (1) document exact color code from the interior factory plate (don't rely on visual color match, factory code is authoritative); (2) confirm color availability through ILVE North America distribution before quoting lead time; (3) quote honestly, if the color is a current stocked color expect 2-4 weeks, if it's a legacy color expect 6-10 weeks; (4) schedule install when the panel delivers, treating interior mechanical service as independent from the panel-sourcing wait. Interior mechanical work (burner service, oven service, control-board service) runs on standard ILVE service-economics pace in parallel with any panel lead time. Panel prices quoted individually, vary by color + specific model trim."
  },
  {
    q: "What does ILVE stove repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Typical ILVE bands: orifice swap (per burner) $180–$280; burner cap replacement $140–$220; spark-module ignition $280–$400; ignitor tip clean / replace $200–$300; thermocouple flame-failure device $220–$320; air-mixture adjustment $180–$260; gas-line regulator $220–$320; gas valve swap $300–$440; oven igniter $260–$380; bake element (dual-fuel electric) $320–$460; convection fan motor $340–$500; temperature sensor $220–$320; thermostat (analog) $280–$400; thermal fuse $240–$340; oven door rope seal $180–$280; control board (digital Majestic III / Panoramagic) $480–$660; color-matched panel quoted individually 2-10 week lead depending on color. ILVE service runs comparable to Viking / Wolf economics, 20-30% above mainstream-brand pricing reflecting specialty Italian parts + diagnostic time."
  },

    {
      q: "Where can I find the official ILVE manual or warranty information?",
      a: `Our technicians work independently of ILVE's factory service network - we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
    },
  ];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, ILVE Stove Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "ILVE Stove Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "ILVE stove repair across Southern California, LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Majestic III, Nostalgie II, Panoramagic, Milano, Roma, Torino, Professional Plus. Italian Treviso family-owned since 1975. 60+ color program with stainless / chrome / brass / copper / bronze knob trim. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "ILVE", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/ilve/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "ILVE Stove Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>ILVE stove service? Same-day across all 5 SoCal counties:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › ILVE › Stove Repair</div>
    <h1>ILVE Stove Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">ILVE is the Italian family-owned stove brand based in Treviso region, founded 1975, independent, distinct from the Guastalla Emilia-Romagna families behind Smeg and Bertazzoni. ILVE's lineup runs from entry-luxury Milano / Roma / Torino through mid-luxury Nostalgie II and Panoramagic to flagship Majestic III and Professional Plus, with 60+ color + finish combinations including stainless / chrome / brass / copper / bronze knob trim that ILVE is specifically known for. In LA, ILVE concentrates in Bel Air + Beverly Hills design-forward custom kitchens, Santa Monica + Venice architectural remodels, Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-district homes, Pasadena + San Marino heritage kitchens where color + handle choice is part of the design brief. Parts through ILVE North America distribution, common service components 5-10 days, Italian factory-sourced specialty parts 2-4 weeks, color-matched panels 2-10 weeks depending on color. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Italian Treviso family-owned since 1975</b>, independent</li>
      <li><b>60+ color program</b> with stainless / chrome / brass / copper / bronze knobs</li>
      <li><b>Majestic III flagship</b>, 30/36/40/48/60 freestanding dual-fuel + all-gas</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>ILVE in LA, Italian family-owned, color + finish as design choice</h2>
    <p>ILVE's Italian family ownership matters more than most buyers realize until they own one for a decade. Because the brand isn't folded into a BSH or Whirlpool or Middleby corporate structure, ILVE product decisions, including color program choices, knob material options, and even service-parts continuity on legacy platforms, stay with the Treviso family. The result: color options that wouldn't survive a corporate portfolio rationalization stay in the catalog because they matter to the specific ILVE design brief. 60+ enamel + hand-finished color combinations with five knob-material options (stainless, chrome, brass, copper, bronze) means households can match a kitchen's specific design rather than choose from a four-color corporate program.</p>
    <p>In LA that's where ILVE's installed base concentrates: households where the stove is a visual focal point and color + finish are part of the design brief, not an afterthought. Red Majestic III in Tuscan-influenced Silver Lake kitchens, burgundy Nostalgie II with brass knobs in Hancock Park heritage homes, pale-blue Panoramagic with chrome in Santa Monica coastal-modern kitchens, matte-black Professional Plus with copper in Venice architectural custom. Service approach on ILVE respects the finish, we protect handles and enamel panels during any work near the exterior, and we source matched parts through Italian factory channels when exterior-adjacent components need replacement. Interior mechanical service runs on standard ILVE service-economics pace in parallel.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>ILVE stove failures our techs see most often</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Gas burner no-light, orifice / spark / thermocouple</h3><p>Most common ILVE service. Orifice $180–$280 per burner on EU-spec or fuel-type mismatch; spark module $280–$400; thermocouple flame-failure $220–$320.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven temperature inaccurate</h3><p>Sensor drift at 5-10 year mark. Sensor $220–$320; analog thermostat $280–$400; digital control board $480–$660.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Convection fan motor noise or failure</h3><p>Dual-fuel electric oven-side. Motor swap $340–$500.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven door rope seal degradation</h3><p>Seal compression at 10+ years allows heat leak. Seal swap $180–$280 per door.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Bake element on dual-fuel electric oven</h3><p>Element swap $320–$460.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Color-matched panel exterior damage</h3><p>Italian factory sourcing. 2-10 week lead depending on color availability. Quoted individually.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>ILVE stove product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Majestic III (flagship)</h3><p>30"/36"/40"/48"/60" dual-fuel + all-gas. 60+ colors. Five knob-trim options. Current-generation ILVE.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Nostalgie II</h3><p>Vintage-inspired rounded-corner styling. Brass / chrome knob detail. Heritage-design kitchens.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Panoramagic</h3><p>Panoramic-view tilt oven-door design. Full-view window. Majestic-platform derivative.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Professional Plus</h3><p>Pro-style flagship. Heavier build. Higher BTU burners. Closer to Viking / Wolf format.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Milano / Roma / Torino</h3><p>Entry-luxury city-named lines. Smaller formats. Narrower color program.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Color + knob program</h3><p>60+ enamel / hand-finished colors. Stainless / chrome / brass / copper / bronze knob trim.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>ILVE vs Smeg vs Bertazzoni, Italian family brands</h2>
    <p>Three Italian family-owned stove brands in LA, distinct geographies + ownership families.</p>
    <p><b>ILVE (this page)</b>, Treviso region (Veneto), family-owned since 1975, freestanding 30-60" dual-fuel + all-gas, 60+ colors, five knob-material options. Distinct from Emilia-Romagna Italian families.</p>
    <p><b>Smeg</b>, Guastalla (Emilia-Romagna), Bermani family since 1948, 60cm European-width signature, Victoria retro + Classic + Dolce Stil Novo lines. See <a href="/brands/smeg-stove-repair/">Smeg stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>Bertazzoni</b>, also Guastalla (Emilia-Romagna), 1882 family 6th generation, Professional Series freestanding 30/36/48, 60+ enamel colors. See <a href="/brands/bertazzoni-stove-repair/">Bertazzoni stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p>Choice drivers: ILVE for widest color / knob-trim program + Majestic III full-lineup; Smeg for 60cm Euro-width + Victoria retro iconography; Bertazzoni for 6th-generation heritage + Professional Series build. Parts networks brand-exclusive.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What ILVE stove repair typically costs</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Orifice swap (per burner)</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>EU / LP / NG mismatch</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Burner cap replacement</td><td>$140 – $220</td><td>Per burner</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Spark-module ignition</td><td>$280 – $400</td><td>ILVE-specific</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Ignitor tip clean / replace</td><td>$200 – $300</td><td>Carbon / electrode wear</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermocouple flame-failure device</td><td>$220 – $320</td><td>EU safety spec</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas-line regulator</td><td>$220 – $320</td><td>Pressure stability</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas valve swap</td><td>$300 – $440</td><td>Stuck / restricted</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Oven igniter</td><td>$260 – $380</td><td>Glow-but-no-heat</td></tr>
